dataLineage.statement:
Layer was to ITOS in an email from UNOCHA, then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following was found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated Admin0, 1 and 2 name and p-code fields. Admin parent attribution has been given according to spatial location. 2. Created and populated reference name field. 3. P-codes, where applicable, have been restored from previous COD. New p-codes have been constructed for new units. 4. Found and fixed 18 gap errors and 19 overlap errors. 5. Fixed small nesting errors between layers. 6. Admin2 name "Nioro du rip" was converted to Proper Case. 7. Admin3 unit "Nguelou" with empty geometry was removed as it was a duplicate unit.
